[[迪克·德賓|迪克·德賓]]記得2018年1月11日於[[椭圆形办公室|椭圆形办公室]]，[[唐納·川普|特朗普]]在評論[[萨尔瓦多|萨尔瓦多]]、[[洪都拉斯|洪都拉斯]]、[[海地|海地]]及[[非洲|非洲]]國家（{{lang-en|African nations}}）之時講說 " 這些[[屎|屎]]洞向我們發送他們不想要的人 (Those '''shitholes''' send us the people that they don’t want)" 
<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.factcheck.org/2018/01/trump-say-immigration-meeting/|title=What Did Trump Say at Immigration Meeting?|first=Eugene|last=Kiely|date=2018-01-16|publisher=|accessdate=2019-03-10|archive-date=2019-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190313064124/https://www.factcheck.org/2018/01/trump-say-immigration-meeting/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。官方並沒有否認，也有人認為特朗普不是講 "shit '''hole'''" 而是講 "屋外廁所（{{link-en|shit '''house'''|Outhouse}}）"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Prokop |first1=Andrew |title=The “shithouse defense,” explained: how Trump’s allies are trying to dig him out of his “shithole” |url=https://www.vox.com/2018/1/16/16897016/trump-shithole-shithouse-countries |website=Vox |accessdate=2019-03-07 |date=2018-01-16 |archive-date=2019-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308003019/https://www.vox.com/2018/1/16/16897016/trump-shithole-shithouse-countries |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此事導致布克 一星期內 大發雷霆<ref>{{cite web |title=Cory Booker blasts Republicans for amnesia over Trump's 'shithole' remark |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/jan/17/cory-booker-blasts-republicans-for-amnesia-over-trumps-shithole-remark |website=The Guardian |publisher=Associated Press |accessdate=2019-03-11 |date=2018-01-17 |7= |archive-date=2019-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308080928/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/jan/17/cory-booker-blasts-republicans-for-amnesia-over-trumps-shithole-remark |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Booker to Nielsen: Your Silence is Complicity|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJeYvCZUDu0|publisher=Associated Press Archive|website=YouTube|date=2018-01-21|accessdate=2019-03-11|archive-date=2021-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508200615/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJeYvCZUDu0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

